Why Tuples Over Lists in MLOps?
Feature	Tuple	List
Immutability	✅ Prevents accidental changes	❌ Can be modified
Performance	✅ Faster, uses less memory	❌ Slower, more memory
Dictionary Keys	✅ Can be used as keys	❌ Cannot be keys
Safety	✅ Thread-safe	❌ Not thread-safe
Serialization	✅ Easier to serialize	❌ More complex
Key Takeaway: Use tuples in MLOps when you need immutable data structures for configurations, metadata, and 
multi-value returns that shouldn't be accidentally modified during pipeline execution.






